developer.gnome.org - Design Notes
==================================

Content and Structure
---------------------

The design has five main sections:

1. Guides

 - platform-overview (from gnomes-devel-docs)
 - accessibility guide
 - HowDoI...? pages

2. Demos

 - platform-demos (gnome-devel-docs)

3. Design

 - hig (gnome-devel-docs)

4. API Reference

 - Selected manuals from git.gnome.org modules
 - Could also import manuals from freedesktop.org or elsewhere?

5. Index

 - All guides, demos, and api reference documentation
 - Includes manuals that aren't selected for includsion be on the API Reference page

Design To Do
------------

 - Search
 - Demo page
 - Translations/language options
